oai_dc:dc.dc:title: SHORT-CRESTED BREAKING WAVES
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Machen, P.C.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: breaking waves
short crested waves
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The likely effects of short-crested (sc) breaking waves on ships and structures are summarised in the case of the simplest non-trivial sc sea at medium/high crossing angle. Typical experimental data of sc breaking wave-height and sc water particle speeds are given at model-scale.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 19 (1984): Proceedings of 19th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Houston, Texas, 1984.; 62
